title: Ukraine Recaptures a Small Village as Russian Forces Retreat
description: The announcement came on the same day that a cargo ship stranded in the Odesa port became the first to venture into the turbulent waters of the Black Sea despite Moscow’s threats to treat vessels in the area as hostile.

title: UK Prime Minister Rishi Sunak’s California Vacation
description: Thanks in part to careful media handling, the British prime minister, who has been criticized for his wife’s wealth and his U.S. ties, survived a trip to California with barely a peep of reproach.

title: Coup in Niger Upends U.S. Terrorism Fight and Could Open a Door for Russia
description: The military takeover could force the Pentagon to withdraw hundreds of American troops and close drone bases in the West African country.

title: Tropical Storm Hilary Will Move Toward Baja California
description: The storm threatens to bring strong winds and heavy rainfall to the Baja California peninsula and the Southwestern United States.

title: In Test of Ukraine’s New Black Sea Corridor, Cargo Ship Travels From Odesa
description: Kyiv is aiming to resume traffic to its seaports despite Russia’s threats to ships moving to and from Ukraine.

title: Two American Tourists Caught Sleeping in the Eiffel Tower
description: The two men posed no threat and were handed over to the police, officials said.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Ukraine Claims Another Small Gain as Counteroffensive Pushes On
description: Ukraine’s deputy defense minister said Kyiv’s forces had recaptured the village of Urozhaine, a small step in its grinding campaign to break through Russian defenses in the south.

title: Russian Drones Attack Ukrainian Port on Danube River
description: Russian drones hit the port of Reni and damaged warehouses used to export grain, Ukrainian officials said.

title: Bank of Ireland Glitch Creates Brief Illusion of Free Money
description: Some A.T.M.s around the country attracted long lines — and a police presence — after customers were apparently allowed to transfer money they did not have.

title: Germany Government Approves Plan to Legalize Some Marijuana Use
description: Germany’s federal cabinet signed off on legalization legislation, but the plan was weaker than the government’s initial proposal.

title: Windmill Made Famous in ‘Chitty Chitty Bang Bang’ Is for Sale in England
description: The property, which was the home of Dick Van Dyke’s character in the 1968 film, is listed for 9 million pounds, or $11.4 million.

title: Thai Court Dismisses Pita’s Renomination
description: Pita Limjaroenrat won a surprise victory in the general election, but his attempts to form a government and become the nation’s next premier have been thwarted.

title: Wednesday Briefing
description: Donald Trump’s response to another criminal indictment.

title: Amid Attacks, Ukraine’s Grain Exports Get a Lifeline From Romania
description: A 40-mile channel, best known outside shipping circles as a magnet for bird watchers, is now a crucial route allowing Ukrainian grain to reach the sea, protected by a NATO umbrella.

title: In France, Some Public Pools Are Victims of Budget Woes
description: As temperatures rise, a vast but aging system is feeling the strains of rising energy costs, increasing water scarcity and mounting pressure on public budgets.

title: Tony Blair, Former U.K. Leader, Is Suddenly Back in Favor
description: The former British prime minister, who left Downing Street widely unpopular, is back in favor with his party, Labour, which hopes his political skills can be an advantage as an election nears.
